stack size is much smaller,

00:58:20.790 --> 00:58:22.860
like let's say you only
have three big blinds,

00:58:22.860 --> 00:58:26.850
then you can drastically
increase this range.

00:58:26.850 --> 00:58:29.250
So when your
effective stack size

00:58:29.250 --> 00:58:33.910
is actually say 10, or let's
say your effective stack size is

00:58:33.910 --> 00:58:39.110
five big blinds, intuitively you
might think, I can wager a lot,

00:58:39.110 --> 00:58:41.570
I can wager a lot
wider range of hands.

00:58:41.570 --> 00:58:42.690
So here's the argument.

00:58:42.690 --> 00:58:46.740
The argument is I'm only
risking five big blinds.

00:58:46.740 --> 00:58:50.070
In the other case I was
risking 12 big blinds.

00:58:50.070 --> 00:58:53.350
I should be way more
aggressive with five big blinds

00:58:53.350 --> 00:58:54.840
than 12 big blinds.

00:58:54.840 --> 00:58:55.830
So that's the argument.

00:58:55.830 --> 00:58:57.660
But the reason why
that argument is wrong

00:58:57.660 --> 00:58:59.610
is because with five
big blinds you're

00:58:59.610 --> 00:59:01.242
going to get called every time.

00:59:01.242 --> 00:59:02.700
With five big blinds
you can't just

00:59:02.700 --> 00:59:04.260
go all in with
seven two off-suit

00:59:04.260 --> 00:59:06.480
because your opponent has
such good odds to call,

00:59:06.480 --> 00:59:07.620
they're going to call you.

00:59:07.620 --> 00:59:10.470
Whereas with 12 big blinds,
even though you're risking more

00:59:10.470 --> 00:59:13.140
you also have more chances
of getting everyone to fold.

00:59:13.140 --> 00:59:15.400
So even though it seems like
you're risking way more,

00:59:15.400 --> 00:59:16.860
in some sense you're not.

00:59:16.860 --> 00:59:19.380
Because the more chips you
are risking the more likely

00:59:19.380 --> 00:59:21.490
it is that everyone else folds.

00:59:21.490 --> 00:59:23.620
Does that argument
make sense to everyone?

00:59:23.620 --> 00:59:24.750
So make sure you don't
get tricked by that

00:59:24.750 --> 00:59:26.166
because it is easy
to get tricked.

00:59:26.166 --> 00:59:29.910
But the fact that when
you're risking more

00:59:29.910 --> 00:59:31.500
you're getting
people to fold more

00:59:31.500 --> 00:59:32.880
means you're
actually not risking

00:59:32.880 --> 00:59:34.970
as much as you think you are.

00:59:34.970 --> 00:59:36.420
And that's a common fallacy.

